apital he was head of client services and business strategy and partner at the firm he started with the firm in  prior to its independent formation as hgcapital he leads the firms client and fundraising activities oversees fund coinvestments and manages the firms business planning and corporate strategy work from  to  he was responsible for all client capitalraising and coinvestment activities  in addition to having overall responsibility for client services and fundraising he coordinates the firms coinvestment activities supervises its investment marketing function and manages firm business planning and strategy activities he is currently working on expanding the firms relationships with other private equity businesses speaking with global institutions and investors about industry trends competitive best practices and their broader longterm strategic plans and engaging with investment banks and financial institutions he joined the private equity division of mercury asset management plc in  his previous roles at prudential ubs investment bank and clarion partners americas llc involved investment acquisitions and dispositions portfolio management financial analysis and client service mr donaldson is the chairman of the evca midmarket council he serves as a member of the babson college board of trustees and was a board member and vice chairman of the european venture capital association and chairman of the evca midmarket council mr donaldson is a frequent speaker on private equity he has  years of investment management experience in advising institutional investors on global alternative investment strategies his professional responsibilities have included asset acquisitions and disposals portfolio management financial analysis sector coverage team management planning group management product development business strategy fundraising and client service he maintains an active program of charitable service and giving with a focus on education mr donaldson holds a degree 